ReadMe

Drill ID: JD_2026_06_W4_EquipmentRentalCenterApp

Class Name: EquipmentRentalCenterApp

Difficulty: Level 3 — Object-Oriented Problem Solving

Estimated Time: 70–90 minutes

Actual Time Taken: 76 minutes

Written by: Chanwoo Park

Problem
Create a campus equipment rental system. The system registers equipment, receives rental
requests, assigns available equipment using polymorphism, tracks rental status, and handles
invalid requests.

Program Flow
The main method creates a RentalCenter, registers equipment, submits requests, assigns
equipment, prints reports, simulates returns, and prints updated reports.

Class Responsibilities
EquipmentRentalCenterApp runs the sample scenario.
RentalCenter coordinates equipment, requests, assignments, validation, and reports.
Equipment stores common equipment state and behavior.
Each child equipment class decides which request type it supports.
RentalRequest stores request data and assigned state.

Object Collaboration
RentalCenter asks each Equipment object whether it can support a RentalRequest.
Equipment changes its own status when rented or returned.
RentalRequest marks itself assigned when equipment is successfully rented.